<subSubSection pageId="111" pageNumber="390" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="111.[752,1345,1915,2338]" pageId="111" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[752,904,1915,1944]" pageId="111" pageNumber="390">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Dalquest" authorityName="Dalquest" authorityYear="1950" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="111" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="latirostris">Peromyscus latirostris Dalquest, 1950</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3818814360" pageId="111" pageNumber="390">“Apetsco, near Xilitla, elevation 2700 feet [= 823 m], San Luis Potosi, México.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="111" pageNumber="390" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="111.[752,1345,1915,2338]" pageId="111" pageNumber="390">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dalquest" authorityYear="1950" box="[752,1020,2033,2062]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="111" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="latirostris">Peromyscus latirostris</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1236,2033,2062]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="111" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furvus">furvus</taxonomicName>
species group. It was considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[753,871,2117,2142]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="111" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furvus">P. furvus</taxonomicName>
; however, recent molecular studies have shown that populations from San Luis Potosi and Querétaro, Mexico, are distinct from populations further south and should be recognized as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dalquest" authorityYear="1950" box="[1182,1336,2270,2299]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="111" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="latirostris">P. latirostris</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[138,984,2348,2377]" pageId="111" pageNumber="390" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761054" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6761054" box="[138,984,2348,2377]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761054/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="111" pageNumber="390" startId="111.[138,310,2348,2377]" targetBox="[137,728,1919,2334]" targetPageId="111">
<paragraph blockId="111.[137,1341,2348,2772]" box="[138,984,2348,2377]" pageId="111" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[138,314,2348,2377]" pageId="111" pageNumber="390">Distribution.</emphasis>
SE San Luis Potosi and NE Querétaro, Mexico.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="111" pageNumber="390" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="111.[137,1341,2348,2772]" pageId="111" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[139,387,2388,2417]" pageId="111" pageNumber="390">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
No specific measurements available. The Wide-rostrum Deermouse is presumably similar to the Blackish Deermouse (
<taxonomicName box="[843,966,2427,2456]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="111" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furvus">P. furvus</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
